{{Infobox wrestling promotion |name = Championship Fighting Alliance |image = CFA Logo.png |caption = Championship Fighting Alliance logo |acronym = CFA |established = 2011 |folded = |style = Mixed martial arts |location = Miami Lakes, Florida |founder = Jorge De La Noval |owner = |parent = |sister = |formerly = |website = }}
{{Update|date=January 2014}} '''Championship Fighting Alliance''' ('''CFA''') is a [[mixed martial arts]] (MMA) based promotion company located in [[Miami Lakes]], [[Florida]]. It was founded by former MMA fighter and promoter Jorge De La Noval<ref>{{cite web|last=Alvarez |first=Armando |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/2013/05/14/3397727/fight-card-at-bankunited-center.html |title=Fight card at BankUnited Center a landmark for CFA founder Jorge de la Noval - Mixed Martial Arts |publisher=MiamiHerald.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref> in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Medina|first=Juan|title=About|url=https://www.facebook.com/championshipfightingalliance/info|publisher=Facebook.com|accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref> It has currently produced 10 live events. [[Fallon Fox]], who currently is signed to fight for CFA, is the first openly [[transgender]] MMA fighter in history.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jacques|first=Juliet|title=Sport is slowly catching up with transgender realities|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/apr/16/sport-catching-up-transgender-realities|publisher=Guardian.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref> On May 24, 2013, CFA will be hosting CFA 11, their 11th event at the Bankunited Center located on the [[University of Miami]] campus.<ref>{{cite web|last=Marrocco|first=Steven|title=Promoter sets CFA 11 for May 24 with Fallon Fox fight planned|url=http://www.mmajunkie.com/news/2013/03/promoter-sets-cfa-11-for-may-24-with-fallon-fox-fight-planned|publisher=Mmajunkie.com|accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref> Fighter 411 reported that CFA had held the most events in Florida during the 2012-2013 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fighter411.com/ |title=Fighter 411 |publisher=Fighter 411 |date= |accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref>
